Apr 26 2009 	Boston Manor Hotel - Very Basic !!	I stayed at this hotel with my relatives in April for a sightseeing tour of London. This hotel is only worth staying in for the one night due to the poor room quality and overall cleanliness . The twin room which I stayed in was very basic with poor mismatched furniture and uncomfortable bed. It was not a room in which you could relax in after a long day sightseeing.The bathroom was very small and unclean. The only positive about this experience is the fact that the hotel has a nice indian restraurant, has parking and is near to a tube station. I know the hotel is situation in London and on reflection is quite reasonably priced. However I do not think that cheap should automatically mean that the accommodation should be small, cramped and unclean.	
Jan 13 2009 	Cheap decent and near Heathrow	I stayed here for one night as I had some work in the city. I paid £55 for a double bed including breakfast which was good value considering that the room was pretty big and also the b/f was good. The hotel is on piccadilly line (10 min walk to tube station) in zone 4. I found that it was good value as it was near the airport with easy access into town (30mins to central london by tube). It was cheaper compared to other budget options like IBIS, premier inn etc.The staff was very helpful, they helped us carry our luggage to our room. We had lots of heavy luggage as we were returning after a long vacation. Also they stored our luggage when were in town before our evening flight. Many chain hotels in London now refuse to store luggage due to security reasons. We were also given complimentary Internet for our room.The place has a reasonabaly priced Indian restaurant where we had our dinner. The food was average. Its a good option if you are tired and dont want to go out I would recommend this hotel to anyone who does not want to pay £100 a night for a room and wants to be near the airport with good access to the center as well. Also because of the size of the room I would recommend this to budget business travellers who want to stay for a longer period.I would stay here again if I am flying to/from Heathrow.	
Aug 15 2008 	Only a 3 rating because its in London	I left it late to book a hotel for my weekend in London so this seriously reduced the choice in the (what I consider) reasonable price range. The best (and nearly only) choice seemed this hotelI picked it mainly because it was the most convenient for the price, close (ish) to the piccadily line &amp; close to a night bus route from central London. In these terms it did everything it needed too- but I have stayed at far more convenient (and better) hotels for less.The public areas of the hotel were dated, tired and in places not overly clean. I too laughed like the previous reviewers at the 'Luxury suite' signs! I cannot imagine what definition of Luxury they have used!The room itself was similar- the delightful net curtains were a lovely shade of yellow &amp; the windows were dirty. I would also bet that this room has recently been smoked in (is this not banned now?).The sheets were worn but were clean &amp; the bed was on the hard side but one of the better hotel beds to sleep in.The bathroom at first appeared clean, but whilst sat on the toilet (sorry!) I noticed nasty looking stains on the door frame (erghh!).The busy road mentioned before didnt affect me (except the drunks at 3.00 am) and I had a decent nights sleep.Breakfast was OK actually- OJ was OK, cooked brekkie not too cheap &amp; nasty- apparently branded cereals.The staff didn't speak much English, and there was a highly embarassing incident on an adjoining table (the customer wanted wholemeal toast- this was incorrect 3 times, ignored twice &amp; then finally it was deduced that they didn't have any!)Didn't make breakfast second day unfortunately but nothing at all to complain about on my part.......Hotel itself is about 10 mins walk to tube one way (with a (shock) decent Harvester on the way if you are hungry. The other way some pubs (polish or Irish- take your pick!) &amp; places to eat. There is also an Indian Restaurant in the hotel itself, but didn't try this out... In the context of London hotels I feel that a 2 rating would be mean for this hotel- I reluctantly give it a 3 because I have stayed at a number of London Hotels in this price range &amp; really it is not bad in comparison. (That said I have given better in Blackpool a 1 rating lol!)Would stay again for the right price, but would look elsewhere first......	
