Aug 13 2007	Unpleasant	If you want a hotel convenient to Heathrow because you're booked on an inconveniently scheduled flight (i.e. 8am departure), forget this place. From the Boston Manor tube stop it's a 15-minute slog of a walk with luggage in tow, and then about a 20-minute tube ride to the terminal (we ended up taking a taxi). It is also really expensive to get in and out of central London (as of this writing, GBP 4 each way). The place is run down and depressing (okay, maybe not by British standards) and the rooms on the front are too noisy with truck traffic for sound sleeping. Breakfast is included in the room rate, but when we asked for some breakfast food the night before because we were departing before their 7am start of breakfast service, they refused (even tho they have a fridge they offered for storing anything we cared to purchase). We had two rooms booked for us and two kids: they upgraded us to a room big enough for all 4 (one full and two twin beds) but refused to let us exchange our reserved two cheaper rooms for that one more expensive one (which would have saved us some dough) even tho we ended up not using the kids' room (they wanted to stay in ours because theirs was far away through a lybranthine arrangement of poky corridors and staircases). The room we did use was cramped with all those beds and the bathroom barely big enough to turn around in. The whole experience was pretty creepy and unpleasant. We'd have done better to have sprung for the Holiday Inn Heathrow or similar, with free van service to the terminal and much more comfortable accommodation. A lousy end to a great visit to England.	
