Nov 25 2005	Will not be going again	I booked two twin rooms for 4 people and was given two rooms, one with four beds and the other with two!! They refused to remove the other two beds.Good points:Car parking space - big plus point, almost guaranteed, there were always spaces when I needed one.Staff were always friendlyBad points:The place was dirty!! the whole place was in need of painting and general refurbishment. There were torn carpets everywhere and dust in all the nooks and crannies.The rooms was also not clean, dust was gathering and there were stains on the carpet. Under the bed was rubbish left by previous guests which the staff had not spotted. The rooms needed an overhaul!!It was freezing!! The heating was sporadic at best and I needed to sleep with a jumper and socks to stay warm.It was noisy, you are able to hear peoples conversations on the street below if they are talking even slightly above normal levels and you are definitely able to hear traffic clearly.Bathroom: Tiny!!! The basin was tiny and it was almost impossible to wash your hands in it. The toilet was placed (presumably to save space) in such a way that your knees were touching the walls in front when you sat on it!!The shower was an electric one that barely ran to a trickle!! Also, it was impossible to control (believe me I tried for almost 20minutes) the temperature. The water was either boiling hot or freezing cold and nothing inbetween.Breakfast: Consists of cereal (help yourself), toast and full english breakfast (one sausage - still raw in the middle, one slice of bacon - although I did not get one unlike the three other members of my group, 2 eggs and 1/8 of a tomato) and tea or coffee.In terms of location, it is 10-15minutes walk to Boston Manor tube station which is 45 minutes approx to Leicester Square. There is an Esso station opposite which is helpful for filling petrol on your return journey.	
